status: Family of braille to which the item belongs. This is not the particular braille code, but the type of braille code used, representing different types of written symbols.

preferred label (en): no specified class of braille writing
definition (en): Item consists of fewer than two specified classes of braille writing.
Braille representation for the alphabet, numbers, and punctuation marks commonly used in general writing.
Braille formatting rules for textbooks and related materials.
Braille representations for symbols employed in mathematics and scientific writing.
Braille representations for symbols used in computer programs, texts, and other computer related materials.
Braille representations for symbols used in notated music.

Class of braille writing other than no specified class of braille writing, literary braille, format code braille, mathematics and scientific braille, computer braille, music braille, multiple braille types.
